		   <tr><td valign="top" id="fs8" class="mform" ><span class="notbold">By:</span> <a href="/db/poster.html?user=268104"><span id=>longears</span></a><b><span id=></span></b><br />7 posts
		   <br /><nobr><span class="notbold">Score</span>: Decent [3.00]</nobr><br /><br /><a href="/cgi-bin/pm.pl?action=addtolist&addname=longears&type=Address" id="fs8"><img src="/shared/plus.gif" border="0" align="middle" height="9" width="9" alt="Add to address book"> Add to address book</a><br /><img src="/shared/transp.gif" width="135" border="0" height="1"></td><td valign="top" class="mform" width="100%"><p>Hi I have a Berserker on Xev name is &quot;Gimli Ragingaxe&quot; he is a dwarf and is at the moment lvl 22. I find this class to be extremly fun. From a dps standpoint I have a epic monk lvl 65, epic rogue lvl 52, and a ranger at lvl 29. <br /><br />These most certainly will hold their own. The class will not replace any other current class but will just a be added DPS class.  <br /><br />My strategy on playing Berserker is leg chop to pull(huge range further than throwing the axe) while incoming throw 2 or 3 axe at mob, then soon as you can head strike which stuns mob, then use frenzy on the stuned mob I find you have a better % chance to score your triples on frenzy if its on a stuned mob( this may just be coinsidence but appears to be that way) wait for frenzy to refresh and repeat. The Stun / frenzy combo works nice.. I find that this will keep mob stuned around 45% of the fight(accounting for a occasional resist on the stun) now at low life you can either keep the stun for the fleeing mob (hope you dont have a fast runner) or my choice is at 25% switch over to leg chop for the snare.<br /><br />All in all I feel they made a new class that was 1st  very fun to play, 2nd a very usefull class with all the stuns &amp; snares .. we didnt really need a healer(we had a 3 zerker,1 cleric,1 mage, 1 shammy group omg the DPS was nasty for our level)<br /><br />Duoing with 2 Zerkers is great also, if you both time your stuns the mob is in a stun lock &amp; will do very little damage to you.<br /><br />all in All thumbs up Sony now lets get a screen shot at least of our epic I hope its a huge frickin axe i mean HUGE with crazy particles coming off from all angles.<br /><br />peace &amp; enjoy<br /></p></td></td></tr><tr><td colspan="2" class="mform"><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" width="100%"><tr><td id="fs8"></td><td align="right" id="fs8" >2 Replies</td></tr></table>
